==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antiquated
<hw>An"ti*qua`ted</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Grown old.
Hence: Bygone; obsolete; out of use; old-fashioned; <as>as, an
<ex>antiquated</ex> law</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Antiquated</xex>
words.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Old Janet, for so he understood his <qex>antiquated</qex>
attendant was denominated.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Ancient; old; antique; obsolete. See
<er>Ancient</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antiquatedness</ent>⟦br⟧
